  "游戏其实就是一个不停转的循环": "A game is really just a loop that never stops spinning",
  "桌面程序大多是「等用户点一下，做一件事，再等」。实时游戏不是——哪怕你什么都不按，敌人还在走、子弹还在飞、动画还在播。所以游戏的核心是一个一直转的循环:每转一圈就是一帧,这一圈里要把整个世界往前推进一点点,再把它画出来。这个循环停了,游戏就「卡死」了。": "Most desktop apps are 'wait for a click, do one thing, wait again'. Real-time games are not — even if you press nothing, enemies keep walking, bullets keep flying, animations keep playing. So a game's core is a loop that never stops: each turn of the loop is one frame, and in that turn you push the whole world forward a little, then draw it. If the loop stops, the game freezes.",
  "为什么必须拆成 update 和 render": "Why update and render must be separate",
  "每一帧逻辑上分两步:update 负责「想」——挪位置、判碰撞、扣血、推进计时器;render 负责「画」——把当前世界状态搬到屏幕上。把它们拆成两个函数,好处很实在:render 不改数据,可以随时换成另一套绘图库;做自动化测试时可以只跑 update、完全不画,照样验证逻辑对不对。混在一起的代码是改不动的。": "Each frame is logically two steps: update does the 'thinking' — move positions, test collisions, subtract health, advance timers; render does the 'drawing' — push the current world state onto the screen. Splitting them into two functions pays off concretely: render touches no data, so you can swap in a different graphics library anytime; in automated tests you can run only update and never draw, yet still verify the logic. Tangled code can't be changed.",
  "update 改世界、render 读世界——职责泾渭分明": "update mutates the world, render reads it — responsibilities cleanly divided",
  "把 render 的参数写成 const，是给自己上的一道保险：万一你手滑想在画图时改数据，编译器会立刻报错。": "Making render's parameter const is insurance for yourself: if you ever slip and try to mutate data while drawing, the compiler flags it immediately.",
  "顺序不能反:先算后画": "Order matters: compute first, draw second",
  "循环体里必须先 update 再 render。反过来的话,你画的是上一帧的旧状态,玩家会觉得画面「慢半拍」。记住这个节奏:推进世界 → 显示世界 → 推进世界 → 显示世界……一圈一圈,这就是主循环。": "Inside the loop you must update before render. Reversed, you'd draw last frame's stale state and the player would feel the screen lag by a beat. Remember the rhythm: advance the world → show the world → advance the world → show the world… round and round — that is the main loop.",
  "最小可运行的主循环:跑满 5 帧": "A minimal runnable main loop: run 5 frames",
