  "「每帧走一格」是个坑": "'One step per frame' is a trap",
  "如果你每帧固定 x += 5,那物体的实际速度就完全取决于「一秒能跑多少帧」。在你的高刷电脑上一秒 240 帧,角色嗖一下飞出屏幕;在别人 30 帧的机器上慢吞吞挪。同一份代码、同一个关卡,体验天差地别。物理速度绝不能和帧率挂钩——这是实时游戏的铁律。": "If you do x += 5 every frame, the object's real speed depends entirely on 'how many frames per second'. On your 240 fps machine the character rockets off-screen; on someone's 30 fps machine it crawls. Same code, same level, wildly different experience. Physics speed must never be tied to frame rate — that's an iron law of real-time games.",
  "dt 就是「这一帧过了多少秒」": "dt is 'how many seconds this frame took'",
  "delta time(dt)是相邻两帧之间真实流逝的时间,单位秒。算法很简单:循环开头记下现在的时间,减去上一帧记下的时间,就是 dt;然后把「现在」存起来,留给下一帧减。有了 dt,位移就按物理公式来:距离 = 速度 × 时间。一秒 100 单位的速度,这一帧过了 0.016 秒,就走 1.6 单位——和帧率无关。": "Delta time (dt) is the real time elapsed between two adjacent frames, in seconds. The algorithm is simple: at the loop start record 'now', subtract the 'last' you recorded previously to get dt, then store 'now' for the next frame to subtract. With dt, displacement follows physics: distance = speed × time. A speed of 100 units/sec over a 0.016 sec frame moves 1.6 units — independent of frame rate.",
  "测出 dt，再用它把速度换算成本帧位移": "Measure dt, then use it to turn speed into this frame's displacement",
  "测时长一定用 steady_clock，它保证单调递增；system_clock 会随系统对时跳变，拿来算 dt 可能算出负数。": "Always use steady_clock for durations — it's guaranteed monotonic; system_clock jumps with clock resyncs and can yield a negative dt.",
  "warning：dt 太大要防穿墙": "warning: clamp huge dt to avoid tunneling",
  "如果某一帧卡了一下(比如切了下窗口、磁盘忙),dt 可能突然变成 0.5 秒。这一帧物体会「瞬移」半秒的距离,直接穿过墙或敌人。专业引擎都会给 dt 设一个上限,比如 if (dt > 0.1f) dt = 0.1f;,宁可这一帧慢动作,也不让它瞬移穿模。": "If a frame stalls (window switch, busy disk), dt may suddenly become 0.5 seconds. That frame teleports the object half a second's worth of distance, tunneling straight through walls or enemies. Professional engines cap dt, e.g. if (dt > 0.1f) dt = 0.1f; — better a slow-motion frame than a teleport through geometry.",
  "永远别假设 dt 很小很稳定。给它设上限是防穿模、防物理炸裂的标准做法。": "Never assume dt is small and steady. Capping it is the standard guard against tunneling and physics blow-ups.",
  "输入处理：每帧采样，按 dt 移动": "Input handling: sample each frame, move by dt",
