  "一帧三步:输入、更新、渲染": "Three steps per frame: input, update, render",
  "完整的一帧有固定顺序:先采输入(玩家这一帧按了什么)、再更新世界(根据输入和 dt 推进)、最后渲染(画出来)。输入必须排第一,因为它是更新的依据。把这三步在主循环里排清楚,你的代码就有了一个所有人都看得懂的骨架。": "A complete frame has a fixed order: sample input (what the player pressed this frame), update the world (advance using input and dt), then render (draw it). Input must come first because it's what update depends on. Lay these three steps out clearly in the main loop and your code gains a skeleton everyone can read.",
  "把输入采成快照，别让逻辑直接摸键盘": "Sample input into a snapshot; don't let logic touch the keyboard",
  "新手常在更新逻辑深处直接写「读键盘」,结果逻辑和操作系统的输入 API 死死缠在一起,既没法测试也没法换平台。正确做法:每帧开头由 process_input 把当前按键状态采集进一个 InputState 结构体快照,update 只接收这个快照。好处一连串:可以喂假输入做单测、可以把一局的输入录下来回放、换平台只改 process_input 一个函数。": "Beginners often write 'read the keyboard' deep inside update logic, fusing the logic to the OS input API — untestable and unportable. The right way: at the start of each frame, process_input captures the current key state into an InputState snapshot, and update receives only that snapshot. The benefits cascade: feed fake input for unit tests, record a session's input for replay, and change only process_input when porting.",
  "输入先成快照，再喂给只认快照的 update": "Turn input into a snapshot first, then feed it to an update that knows only the snapshot",
  "InputState 用一组 bool（left/right/jump…）就够了。让 update 完全不知道键盘的存在，是干净架构的标志。": "A handful of bools (left/right/jump…) is enough for InputState. Keeping update entirely unaware that a keyboard exists is the mark of clean architecture.",
  "移动同样要乘 dt": "Movement must multiply by dt too",
  "别忘了上一课的教训:即使是玩家控制的移动,也要乘 dt。按住右键时 w.x += w.speed * dt,而不是裸的 w.x += 5。否则在高刷屏上角色会快得离谱。输入决定「方向」,dt 决定「这一帧走多远」,两者缺一不可。": "Don't forget last lesson's lesson: even player-controlled movement must multiply by dt. While holding right, do w.x += w.speed * dt, not a bare w.x += 5. Otherwise the character is absurdly fast on a high-refresh screen. Input decides the direction, dt decides how far this frame goes — you need both.",
  "同时按左和右时，两段加减会抵消，物体原地不动——这是对的，正说明输入快照和 dt 解耦得很干净。": "Holding left and right together cancels out and the object stays put — that's correct, and proof the input snapshot and dt are cleanly decoupled.",
  "整合：固定步长的完整主循环": "Integrate: a fixed-timestep main loop",
  "整合": "Capstone",
  "把输入、固定步长 update、渲染拼成一个完整循环：用累加器 accumulator 攒够时间就以固定 FIXED_DT 步进 update，并在循环顶部采输入、底部渲染。": "Assemble input, fixed-step update, and render into one complete loop: use an accumulator to step update at a fixed FIXED_DT whenever enough time accrues, sampling input at the top and rendering at the bottom.",
  "顺序仍是输入→更新→渲染：先 process_input，再用 while 把累加器里攒够的时间一步步喂给 update，最后 render 一次。": "The order is still input→update→render: process_input first, then a while loop spends the accumulated time into update step by step, then render once.",
  "累加器是关键：accumulator += dt 把真实流逝的时间存进去；while (accumulator >= FIXED_DT) { update(...); accumulator -= FIXED_DT; } 把它按固定步长花出去。": "The accumulator is key: accumulator += dt banks the real elapsed time; while (accumulator >= FIXED_DT) { update(...); accumulator -= FIXED_DT; } spends it in fixed steps.",
  "update 永远传 FIXED_DT，不是 dt——这正是「固定步长」的含义：每一步物理都走相同的时间。": "Always pass FIXED_DT to update, never dt — that's exactly what 'fixed timestep' means: every physics step advances the same amount of time.",
  "循环顶部采输入存进 InputState": "Sample input into an InputState at the top",
  "每帧先用 InputState in = process_input(frame); 拿到输入快照。": "Each frame, do InputState in = process_input(frame); to get the input snapshot.",
  "把 dt 累加进 accumulator": "Accumulate dt into the accumulator",
  "用 accumulator += dt 把这一帧的真实时间存进累加器。": "Use accumulator += dt to bank this frame's real time into the accumulator.",
