  "写 while (accumulator >= FIXED_DT) 循环来按固定步长更新。": "Write a while (accumulator >= FIXED_DT) loop to update in fixed steps.",
  "以 FIXED_DT 步进并扣减": "Step by FIXED_DT and subtract it",
  "每步用 update(world, in, FIXED_DT) 更新，并 accumulator -= FIXED_DT。": "Each step calls update(world, in, FIXED_DT) and does accumulator -= FIXED_DT.",
  "可变步长够用，但物理会抖": "Variable timestep works, but physics gets jittery",
  "前面我们用真实 dt 直接驱动 update,这叫「可变步长」,简单够用。但它有隐患:dt 每帧都不一样,物理积分(尤其是碰撞、弹簧、堆叠)会因步长抖动而表现不稳;更要命的是,同一段操作在不同机器上算出的结果可能不完全一致——联机游戏里这会直接导致两边画面对不上。": "So far we drove update with the real dt directly — 'variable timestep', simple and adequate. But it has pitfalls: dt differs every frame, so physics integration (especially collisions, springs, stacking) becomes unstable as the step jitters; worse, the same sequence of actions can compute slightly differently across machines — in multiplayer this desyncs the two screens outright.",
  "固定步长:物理永远走一样大的步": "Fixed timestep: physics always takes equal steps",
  "固定步长把渲染和物理解耦。物理永远以一个恒定的 FIXED_DT(比如 1/50 秒)前进。做法是用一个「累加器」:每帧把真实流逝的时间倒进累加器,然后只要累加器里攒够了一个 FIXED_DT,就步进一次物理、扣掉一个 FIXED_DT,反复直到不够。一帧渲染只画一次,但物理可能步进 0 次、1 次或好几次。这样无论渲染快慢,物理的步长永远恒定,结果可复现。": "Fixed timestep decouples rendering from physics. Physics always advances by a constant FIXED_DT (say 1/50 sec). The trick is an accumulator: each frame, pour the real elapsed time into it, then while it holds at least one FIXED_DT, step physics once and subtract one FIXED_DT, repeating until it can't. Rendering draws once per frame, but physics may step 0, 1, or several times. So no matter the render speed, the physics step is always constant and the result reproducible.",
  "累加器把真实时间切成等长的物理步": "The accumulator slices real time into equal physics steps",
  "余下不足一步的时间会留在 accumulator 里，带到下一帧——一点都不浪费，这正是固定步长稳定的原因。": "Leftover time below one step stays in the accumulator and carries to the next frame — nothing is wasted, and that's precisely why fixed timestep stays stable.",
  "拼起来:一个完整的实时主循环": "Put it together: a complete real-time main loop",
  "至此四课收束成一个骨架:测 dt → 采输入 → 用累加器以固定步长跑 update → 渲染。这就是从《超级马里奥》到现代引擎都在用的同一套结构。记住这个次序和分工:时间测量在最外,输入在更新之前,物理在固定步长里跑,渲染在每帧末尾各画一次。把这套骨架刻进肌肉记忆,以后接任何图形库(SDL、SFML、自研引擎)都只是往这四个槽里填实现而已。": "Now all four lessons collapse into one skeleton: measure dt → sample input → run update in fixed steps via the accumulator → render. This is the very structure used from Super Mario to modern engines. Remember the order and division of labor: time measurement outermost, input before update, physics inside fixed steps, render once at the frame's end. Burn this skeleton into muscle memory, and adopting any graphics library (SDL, SFML, your own engine) is just filling these four slots with implementations.",
  "别给 update 传 dt 代替 FIXED_DT——那样就退回可变步长，整个固定步长结构白搭了。": "Don't pass dt to update instead of FIXED_DT — that reverts to variable timestep and defeats the whole fixed-step structure.",
